name: BlindBites: Taste it. Find it
description:
BlindBites: Taste It. Find It. is a fun and exciting team event where two members are tied back-to-back and blindfolded. 
One member tastes the mystery food item placed in front of them and gives hints to the other member without revealing the exact name of the item. 
The second member must identify the food item based on the hints.

name: AI Mystery Box Challenge
description:
The AI Mystery Box Challenge is a one-day technical event designed to test participants’ 
analytical thinking, creativity, and practical skills in Artificial Intelligence and Machine 
Learning. This event offers a unique, problem-solving experience where teams are challenged 
with an unknown AI task revealed only at the start of the competition. 
Participants will receive a mystery box containing a real-world dataset and a problem 
statement. Once the box is opened upon official announcement, teams must quickly analyze the 
problem, design an appropriate machine learning solution, and develop a working model within 
the given time. To enhance practical applicability, teams are also required to integrate their 
model with a functional web interface, simulating industry-level AI deployment. 

The event encourages collaborative teamwork, effective time management, and hands- 
on implementation of AI concepts such as data preprocessing, model selection, training, 

evaluation, and deployment. With internet access permitted, participants can explore libraries, 
frameworks, and documentation to refine their solutions. 

The AI Mystery Box Challenge will be conducted at AI Lab 2 with a registration fee of 
₹250 per head. This event is ideal for students who are passionate about AI, Data Science, and 
real-time problem solving, and who wish to showcase their technical expertise in a competitive 
environment.

description:
A technical project presentation competition where teams (1-3 members) showcase innovative projects in engineering, technology, or innovation. 
Each team gets 10 minutes to present and 5 minutes for Q&A, with originality being crucial. 
A Q&A session helps evaluate technical depth and communication skills. 
The winning team will be awarded with cash prize, and attendance is mandatory for certification.

name: Agentic AI
description:
The one-day workshop on “Agentic AI” is designed to provide participants with in-depth 
knowledge of intelligent AI agents capable of autonomous decision-making, goal-oriented behavior, 
and real-world problem solving. The workshop will explore how Agentic AI systems operate beyond 
traditional AI models by enabling planning, reasoning, and adaptive actions in dynamic environments. 
The session will be led by Mr. Dineshkumar Shanmugam, Founder & CEO of Wildrise, Korclub 
Consumer Private Limited, who brings strong industry experience in building AI-driven products and 
scalable technology solutions. Through expert-led lectures, real-world use cases, and interactive 
discussions, participants will gain valuable insights into the architecture, applications, and future 

scope of Agentic AI across industries such as automation, business intelligence, robotics, and smart 
systems. 
This workshop is ideal for students and faculty interested in Artificial Intelligence, Data Science, 
Machine Learning, and emerging intelligent systems. It aims to bridge the gap between theoretical AI 
concepts and practical implementation, encouraging innovation and hands-on learning. 
The workshop will be conducted at AB Lab 2 and is open to all interested participants with a 
registration fee of ₹300 per head.

name: Chip2Test
description:
This hands-on workshop will guide students through the journey of VLSI design, from logic design to the implementation of test patterns using DFT techniques. 
Participants will gain practical experience in identifying faults, creating test strategies, and understanding how DFT ensures reliability and efficiency in modern chip design. 
By the end of the session, students will have a clear understanding of the role of DFT in bridging design and verification in real-world VLSI circuits.

name: IPL AUCTION
description:
The IPL Auction is an exciting and strategic event designed to simulate the real-life Indian 
Premier League player auction, offering participants a thrilling blend of sports knowledge, 
planning, and decision-making. This event challenges teams to build a balanced and competitive 
cricket squad within a limited virtual budget. 

Participants will step into the role of franchise owners, carefully analyzing player statistics, 
roles, and category constraints before making strategic bidding decisions. With a strong 
emphasis on team coordination, financial management, and quick thinking, the event 
provides an engaging experience for cricket enthusiasts and strategy lovers alike.

name: AI MEME CONTEST
description:
The AI Meme Contest is a fun-filled one-day non-technical event that blends creativity, 
humor, and artificial intelligence concepts. This event provides participants with an exciting 

platform to express their ideas and perspectives on AI through visually engaging and thought- 
provoking memes. 

Participants will be given specific AI-related content or themes, based on which they 

must design an original meme that is both entertaining and relevant. Whether created using AI- 
based design tools or manual editing software, originality of the concept is mandatory. The 

contest encourages creative thinking while maintaining ethical standards and responsible content 
creation. 
The AI Meme Contest aims to promote innovation, digital creativity, and expressive 
communication in a light-hearted competitive environment. The event will be conducted at AB 
408, with a registration fee of ₹150 per participant, and is open to individuals or teams looking 

to showcase their creative talents in a non-technical setting.

name: Github Essentials : Code Commit Collaborate
description: This hands-on workshop introduces college students to Git and GitHub for efficient version control and team-based development, covering repositories, commits, branching, merging, and conflict resolution through live demos and practice, while engaging participants in real-world workflows like collaboration and code reviews, ultimately preparing them to confidently use Git and GitHub for academic, internship, hackathon, and industry-level projects.

name: Innovations in Smart and Green Intelligent Engineering Systems
